TITLE: Path Matching with Parameters in Next.js
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to use path matching with parameters in Next.js headers configuration.  The `source` path `/blog/:slug` captures the `slug` parameter, which can then be used in the header `key` or `value`. This allows for dynamic header values based on the matched route.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/05-api-reference/05-config/01-next-config-js/headers.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
