TITLE: Memoizing Fetch Requests in Next.js - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how Next.js automatically memoizes `fetch` requests with identical URLs and options, preventing redundant network requests within a React component tree on the server. This snippet does not introduce any unique dependencies beyond standard TypeScript and Next.js environment configurations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-building-your-application/04-caching/index.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
async function getItem() {
  // The `fetch` function is automatically memoized and the result
  // is cached
  const res = await fetch('https://.../item/1')
  return res.json()
}

// This function is called twice, but only executed the first time
const item = await getItem() // cache MISS

// The second call could be anywhere in your route
const item = await getItem() // cache HIT
```

