TITLE: Time-based Revalidation with App Router in Next.js (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows time-based revalidation for a blog posts list page using the App Router in Next.js with JavaScript. It sets a revalidation time of 1 hour and fetches the latest blog posts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-building-your-application/02-data-fetching/04-incremental-static-regeneration.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export const revalidate = 3600 // invalidate every hour

export default async function Page() {
  const data = await fetch('https://api.vercel.app/blog')
  const posts = await data.json()
  return (
    <main>
      <h1>Blog Posts</h1>
      <ul>
        {posts.map((post) => (
          <li key={post.id}>{post.title}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </main>
  )
}
```

