TITLE: Exporting structuredError Function
DESCRIPTION: Exports the structuredError function which prepares error objects with refined information using getProperError and parsed stack trace. Inputs the error object and outputs a structured error format with name, message, and stack.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/turbopack/crates/turbopack-ecmascript/tests/tree-shaker/analyzer/ipc-index/output.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
export function structuredError(e) {
    e = getProperError(e);
    return {
        name: e.name,
        message: e.message,
        stack: typeof e.stack === "string" ? parseStackTrace(e.stack) : []
    };
}
```

