TITLE: Structured Error Handler Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Creates a structured error object with name, message, and parsed stack trace. Uses getProperError for error normalization and parseStackTrace for stack parsing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/turbopack/crates/turbopack-ecmascript/tests/tree-shaker/analyzer/failed-3/output.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export function structuredError(e) {
    e = getProperError(e);
    return {
        name: e.name,
        message: e.message,
        stack: typeof e.stack === "string" ? parseStackTrace(e.stack) : []
    };
}
```

