TITLE: Importing Next.js Route Module Dependencies
DESCRIPTION: A collection of module import parts for Next.js route modules with TurboPack. These code snippets represent different parts of the module system, importing necessary dependencies and exporting them with TurboPack variable assertions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/turbopack/crates/turbopack-ecmascript/tests/tree-shaker/analyzer/template-pages/output.md#2025-04-21_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import '../../server/future/route-modules/pages/module.compiled';
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import "__TURBOPACK_PART__" assert {
    __turbopack_part__: 0
};
import { PagesRouteModule } from '../../server/future/route-modules/pages/module.compiled';
export { PagesRouteModule as a } from "__TURBOPACK_VAR__" assert {
    __turbopack_var__: true
};
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import "__TURBOPACK_PART__" assert {
    __turbopack_part__: 0
};
import '../../server/future/route-kind';
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import "__TURBOPACK_PART__" assert {
    __turbopack_part__: 2
};
import { RouteKind } from '../../server/future/route-kind';
export { RouteKind as b } from "__TURBOPACK_VAR__" assert {
    __turbopack_var__: true
};
```

